This project automates the credit card application assessment process using logistic regression, a supervised machine learning algorithm designed for binary classification. By analyzing historical applicant data—including demographic, employment, and financial details—the model predicts the probability of approval or rejection, providing a scalable alternative to manual, error-prone evaluation methods. The project encompasses essential data pre-processing steps, such as handling missing values and feature scaling, followed by model training and performance validation using metrics like accuracy, precision, and recall. Ultimately, 
the system provides a robust, interpretable baseline 
for financial institutions to improve decision-making speed and mitigate credit risk.

